                "panel_4_heading": "Why is my honey crystallised?",
                "panel_4_content": "<p>Crystallisation is nature's seal of approval. Real, raw honey crystallizes over time — it's a sign that it hasn't been over-processed or adulterated. The glucose in honey naturally separates and forms crystals, while the flavour and nutrients remain completely intact. If your honey has crystallized, it's doing exactly what pure honey should. To bring it back to liquid form, simply place the jar in warm water (not boiling) and stir gently. Never microwave — it destroys the enzymes that make raw honey special.</p>",
                "panel_5_heading": "Our Beekeepers",
                "panel_5_content": "<p>Every jar of Nectar & Comb honey is sourced from small-scale, independent beekeepers across India's most pristine regions. Our beekeepers follow traditional, chemical-free practices — no antibiotics, no artificial feeding, no shortcuts. They work in harmony with the seasons, allowing bees to forage freely and produce honey at their own pace. This is honey the way it was always meant to be made.</p>",
                "panel_6_heading": "Shipping & Delivery",
                "panel_6_content": "<p>We ship across India with care — every jar is packed to ensure it arrives safely. Orders are dispatched within 1–2 business days. Standard delivery takes 4–7 business days depending on your location. All orders are tracked and you'll receive updates via email. For any delivery concerns, reach us at info@farmure.in.</p>",
